---
// src/pages/blog/swimming-pool-maintenance-beginners.astro
// Drop this file into your src/pages/blog/ folder
// Drop pool-maintenance-hero.webp into your public/images/ folder

const title = "Swimming Pool Maintenance for Beginners";
const description = "Learn the essential chemicals, tools, and routines every pool owner needs to keep their water clean, safe, and looking great year-round.";
const publishDate = "2025-07-13";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>{title} | GK Swimming Pools</title>
  <meta name="description" content={description} />
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />

  <!-- Open Graph -->
  <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
  <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
  <meta property="og:image" content="/images/pool-maintenance-hero.webp" />
  <meta property="og:type" content="article" />

  <!-- Schema: BlogPosting -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BlogPosting",
      "headline": title,
      "description": description,
      "datePublished": publishDate,
      "author": {
        "@type": "LocalBusiness",
        "name": "GK Swimming Pools",
        "telephone": "(818) 804-8204"
      },
      "publisher": {
        "@type": "LocalBusiness",
        "name": "GK Swimming Pools",
        "url": "https://gkswimmingpools.com"
      },
      "image": "https://gkswimmingpools.com/images/pool-maintenance-hero.webp",
      "mainEntityOfPage": {
        "@type": "WebPage",
        "@id": "https://gkswimmingpools.com/blog/swimming-pool-maintenance-beginners"
      }
    })}
  </script>

  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat:wght@400;600;700;800&family=Lato:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />

  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    :root {
      --blue: #084184;
      --aqua: #5CE1E6;
      --white: #ffffff;
      --light-bg: #f0f8ff;
      --muted: #5a6a7a;
    }
    body { font-family: "Lato", sans-serif; background: var(--white); color: #1a1a2e; line-height: 1.8; }

    /* NAV */
    nav { background: var(--blue); padding: 1rem 2rem; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; }
    nav .logo { font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-weight: 800; color: var(--white); font-size: 1.2rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-decoration: none; }
    nav .logo span { color: var(--aqua); }
    nav a.phone { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    nav a.phone:hover { color: var(--aqua); }

    /* HERO */
    .hero { position: relative; height: 480px; overflow: hidden; }
    .hero img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: center top; display: block; }
    .hero-overlay {
      position: absolute; inset: 0;
      background: linear-gradient(to right, rgba(8,65,132,0.88) 0%, rgba(8,65,132,0.45) 60%, transparent 100%);
      display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; padding: 3rem 4rem;
    }
    .hero-eyebrow { font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--aqua); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; color: var(--white); line-height: 1.15; max-width: 560px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
    .hero-meta { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: center; }
    .hero-meta span { font-size: 0.82rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); font-weight: 600; }
    .hero-meta .dot { width: 4px; height: 4px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--aqua); }

    /* LAYOUT */
    .container { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }

    /* INTRO */
    .intro-callout { background: var(--light-bg); border-left: 4px solid var(--aqua); padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin: 3rem 0; }
    .intro-callout p { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--blue); font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }

    /* ARTICLE */
    article { padding: 0 0 4rem; }
    .section-block { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .section-label { display: inline-flex; font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--aqua); background: var(--blue); padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem; border-radius: 2px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    h2 { font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-size: 1.55rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--blue); line-height: 1.25; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    p { font-size: 1rem; color: #2d3748; margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.85; }

    /* CARDS */
    .cards-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .card { background: var(--white); border: 1.5px solid #dce8f5; border-top: 3px solid var(--aqua); border-radius: 4px; padding: 1.25rem; }
    .card-title { font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--blue); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
    .card p { font-size: 0.84rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }

    /* TOOLS */
    .tool-list { list-style: none; margin: 1.25rem 0; }
    .tool-list li { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 0.75rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #edf2f7; font-size: 0.95rem; color: #2d3748; line-height: 1.6; }
    .tool-list li::before { content: ""; width: 8px; height: 8px; min-width: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--aqua); margin-top: 0.5rem; }
    .tool-list strong { color: var(--blue); }

    /* TIP BOX */
    .tip-box { background: var(--blue); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.75rem 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .tip-box .tip-label { font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--aqua); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .tip-box p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; }

    /* DIVIDER */
    .divider { border: none; border-top: 2px solid #edf2f7; margin: 2.5rem 0; }

    /* CTA */
    .cta-banner { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--blue) 0%, #0a5299 100%); padding: 3.5rem 2rem; text-align: center; margin-top: 1rem; }
    .cta-banner h3 { font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .cta-banner p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
    .cta-btn { display: inline-block; background: var(--aqua); color: var(--blue); font-family: "Montserrat", sans-serif; font-weight: 800; font-size: 0.9rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 0.9rem 2.5rem; border-radius: 3px; text-decoration: none; }

    /* FOOTER */
    footer { background: #05305f; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.8rem; }
    footer strong { color: var(--aqua); }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .hero-overlay { padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
      .hero { height: 360px; }
      .container { padding: 0 1.25rem; }
      .cards-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <a href="/" class="logo">GK <span>Swimming Pools</span></a>
  <a href="tel:8188048204" class="phone">(818) 804-8204</a>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <img
    src="/images/pool-maintenance-hero.webp"
    alt="Pool cleaning chemicals and tools laid out on a wooden pool deck"
    width="1200"
    height="480"
    loading="eager"
    fetchpriority="high"
  />
  <div class="hero-overlay">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">GK Swimming Pools &mdash; Pool Care Guide</div>
    <h1>Swimming Pool Maintenance for Beginners</h1>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span>GK Swimming Pools</span>
      <div class="dot"></div>
      <span>7 min read</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<article>
  <div class="container">

    <div class="intro-callout">
      <p>Owning a swimming pool is one of the best things about living in a warm climate &mdash; but keeping it clean, safe, and looking great requires a consistent routine. Whether you manage your pool yourself or work with a professional, understanding the basics will save you time, money, and a lot of frustration down the road.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- CHEMICALS -->
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-label">Foundation</div>
      <h2>Pool Chemicals: What You Need and Why</h2>
      <p>Chemicals are the foundation of any clean swimming pool. Without the right balance, no amount of cleaning will keep your water safe and clear. Here are the essentials every pool owner should have on hand.</p>
      <div class="cards-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-title">Chlorine</div>
          <p>The most essential pool chemical. Sanitizes water by killing bacteria, viruses, and algae. Available as tablets, granules, or liquid.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-title">pH Adjusters</div>
          <p>Keep your water in the 7.3&ndash;7.6 range where chlorine works best. Use pH increaser or decreaser (muriatic acid) as needed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-title">Pool Shock</div>
          <p>A heavy chlorine dose to knock out algae or recover your water after heavy use, a rainstorm, or a chemical imbalance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-title">Algaecide</div>
          <p>Acts as a preventative barrier against algae growth between treatments. Best used consistently, not reactively.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-title">Phosphate Remover</div>
          <p>Especially important if your pool is surrounded by trees. Decomposing leaves raise phosphate levels, which feeds algae growth.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider" />

    <!-- TOOLS -->
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-label">Equipment</div>
      <h2>The Tools Every Pool Owner Should Have</h2>
      <p>The right tools make pool maintenance faster and more effective. These are the essentials worth investing in from day one.</p>
      <ul class="tool-list">
        <li><span><strong>Telescopic Pole</strong> &mdash; The backbone of most cleaning tasks. Connects to skimmer nets, brushes, and vacuums so you can reach every corner of your pool.</span></li>
        <li><span><strong>Skimmer Net</strong> &mdash; Removes leaves and debris from the surface before they sink and start breaking down in the water.</span></li>
        <li><span><strong>Pool Brush</strong> &mdash; Scrubs the walls and floor to prevent algae from taking hold and stops calcium buildup over time. Consistent brushing is one of the simplest ways to protect your plaster.</span></li>
        <li><span><strong>Pool Vacuum</strong> &mdash; Manual or automatic. Cleans debris and dirt settled on the floor that your filter alone cannot handle.</span></li>
      </ul>
      <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-label">Pro Tip</div>
        <p>Water that is too acidic slowly eats away at plaster. Water that is too alkaline causes scaling and discoloration. Consistent brushing paired with balanced chemistry is what keeps your plaster looking great for years.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider" />

    <!-- TESTING -->
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-label">Monitoring</div>
      <h2>Water Testing: You Cannot Manage What You Cannot Measure</h2>
      <p>A reliable water testing kit is just as important as any chemical or tool. Testing two to three times a week gives you an accurate picture of where your chemistry stands so you can make small adjustments before they turn into bigger problems.</p>
      <p>At minimum, your routine should cover pH, chlorine levels, total alkalinity, and phosphates. Small corrections made early are far easier and cheaper than recovering a pool that has gone green.</p>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider" />

    <!-- FILTER -->
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-label">Equipment Care</div>
      <h2>Filter Maintenance and Pump Runtime</h2>
      <p>Your filter is one of the hardest-working parts of your pool system. Whether you have a sand, DE, or cartridge filter, the principle is the same: a clean filter means better water circulation and cleaner water overall. Neglecting your filter puts strain on your pump and reduces the effectiveness of your chemicals.</p>
      <p>Keep an eye on your pressure gauge and clean the filter when pressure rises 8 to 10 PSI above its normal baseline.</p>
      <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-label">Easy Win</div>
        <p>Run your pump at least 8 hours a day to keep water fully circulated and filtered. Stagnant water is much harder to balance and gives algae exactly the conditions it needs to thrive.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider" />

    <!-- CONSISTENCY -->
    <div class="section-block">
      <div class="section-label">The Bottom Line</div>
      <h2>Consistency Is Everything</h2>
      <p>Staying consistent with chemicals, testing, brushing, and filter care is what separates a pool that always looks inviting from one that constantly battles algae, cloudy water, and equipment problems.</p>
      <p>If the routine ever feels overwhelming, or your pool is giving you trouble that basic maintenance is not solving, a professional pool maintenance service can step in, assess the situation, and get everything back on track. The goal is always the same: clean water, healthy chemistry, and a pool that you actually want to use.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="cta-banner">
    <h3>Leave It to the Pros</h3>
    <p>GK Swimming Pools has been serving the San Fernando Valley and Santa Clarita for years. Let us handle the chemistry so you can enjoy the water.</p>
    <a href="tel:8188048204" class="cta-btn">Call (818) 804-8204</a>
  </div>
</article>

<footer>
  &copy; 2025 <strong>GK Swimming Pools</strong> &mdash; Serving the San Fernando Valley &amp; Santa Clarita
</footer>

</body>
</html>
